The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, March 04, 2003 				 Haldia Petro assurance
																								New Delhi, March 3 (PTI): The Centre is committed to the development of Haldia Petrochemicals Limited (HPL), finance minister Jaswant Singh told Bengal chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee at a meeting here today.																								Asked if the assurance meant Gail would be persuaded to pick up equity in the project, Singh said: When I say we are committed, it includes all related issues.																								Revenue generated from the tea cess will be used to improve plantations, Singh said after the meeting where issues related Bengals development were discussed.
